        </section>
        <section>
          <title>China's real estate timeline</title>
          <chapter>
            <paragraph>Looking back to understand the housing boom: 20 years ago China’s real estate market almost didn’t exist.
            </paragraph>
            <paragraph>
              <list type="unordered">
                <item>1990 - SERIES OF REFORMS: Let people buy their government-owned houses at favorable rates.</item>
                <item>2000 - MORE HOME OWNERS: Real estate market was set to boom.</item>
                <item>2010 - CHINA ON THE TOP: China is the largest realty market in the world.</item>
                <item>2016 - BUBBLE RISK: China shows a risky situation similar to the US 2008 bubble.</item>
              </list>
            </paragraph>
          </chapter>
